The HTML Boilerplate

<!DOCTYPE html> -it tells browser that is written in html5
<html lang="en"> -root of the document (lang = language)
<head> -important elements (for us not for the user, no content)
<meta charset="UTF-8"> -character setting, it makes sure the characters display correctly
<title>My Website</title> -title that displays in the tab bar
</head> -important elements (for us not for the user, no content)

<body> -inside it goes the content of the website
<h1>Hello World!</h1>
</body> -inside it goes the content of the website
</html> -root of the document

Shortcut for it
! (but the file has to be save as .html)
